TITLE

     Zaphod - A Binary File Editor

VERSION

     Release 1.0   (update to 1.0 beta and 1.0 gamma)

AUTHOR

     Holger Schemel

     EMail:
     aeglos@valinor.ms.sub.org
     aeglos@uni-paderborn.de
     q99492@pbhrzx.uni-paderborn.de

DESCRIPTION

     Zaphod is a binary file editor (like the good old FileZAP)
     that has the following features:

          - opens on Workbench, on public or own screen
          - AppIcon and AppWindow support
          - multiple files can be edited at the same time
          - full font sensitivity
          - choose your own fonts for the program
          - 7 special fonts are included
          - window resizeable
          - full clipboard support (cut&paste between several
            loaded files or with other applications)
          - supports localization (german catalog included)
          - undo functions
          - search and replace functions
          - saves configuration in the program icon (Tool-Types)
          - can be started from Workbench or from Shell
          - all functions usable with mouse and keyboard
          - documentation in german and english (DVI & ASCII)
          - source code available on request
          - etc. etc. 

SPECIAL REQUIREMENTS

     Amiga OS 2.0 (or higher) required.

     Amiga OS 2.1 (or higher) recommended if you want to
     use the german localization catalog.

